In [105]:
# Create a pivot table with teams as rows and tournament names as columns, counting the number of times each team won
wins_by_team = pd.pivot_table(merged_df[merged_df['Award Name'] == 'Winner'], 
                              index=['Team Name'], columns=['Tournament Name'], 
                              values='Award Id', aggfunc='count', fill_value=0)

# Sum the number of wins across all tournaments and sort the resulting Series in descending order
total_wins_by_team = wins_by_team.sum(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=False)

# Print the resulting Series
print(total_wins_by_team)

In [106]:
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a pivot table of number of wins per team
win_counts = merged_df.pivot_table(index='Team Name', values='Award Id', aggfunc='count')

# Sort the pivot table by number of wins in descending order
win_counts = win_counts.sort_values(by='Award Id', ascending=False)

# Create the bar plot using seaborn
sns.barplot(x=win_counts.index, y='Award Id', data=win_counts, color='b')

# Set the plot title and axis labels
plt.title('Number of Wins per Team')
plt.xlabel('Team Name')
plt.ylabel('Number of Wins')

# Rotate the x-axis labels for better visibility
plt.xticks(rotation=90)

# Display the plot
plt.show()

Then, Who is 'Underdog'?¶

In [142]:
# Create a pivot table to count the number of wins per team
win_counts = pd.pivot_table(merged_df, values='Award Id', index='Home Team Name', aggfunc='count')

# Calculate the 30th percentile of win counts
win_count_30pct = win_counts.quantile(0.3)[0]

# Filter the win_counts dataframe to only include the top 5 teams with the highest win counts
top_teams = win_counts.nlargest(5, 'Award Id').index.tolist()

# Filter the merged dataframe to only include matches where a top team played
top_team_matches = merged_df[(merged_df['Home Team Name'].isin(top_teams)) | (merged_df['Away Team Name'].isin(top_teams))]
In [143]:
# Create a countplot of top teams by tournament without hue
sns.countplot(x='Tournament Name', data=top_team_matches)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title('Number of Matches Played by Top Teams by Tournament')
plt.show()

plt.show()
